INSERT INTO manager_catalogitem VALUES (100010, 'EF-X20 Shoe Mount Flash', 'Fujifilm', 228.99, 100.00, 0.05, '<h2 style="margin-top: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; font-size: 2rem; color: rgb(37, 37, 37); font-family: proxima-nova, ''Helvetica Neue'', helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 2.2rem;">Details</h2><div class="std" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: proxima-nova, ''Helvetica Neue'', helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 29.42943000793457px;"><p style="margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; outline: none;">The&nbsp;<strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; color: rgb(37, 37, 37);">Fuji EF-X20 Shoe Mount Flash</strong>&nbsp;is compact and lightweight with exceptional flash performance! The special external flash (GN20) is designed to match the distinctive body styling of the X Series while ensuring natural shooting. One dial lets you choose between two modes. Auto automatically optimizes flash for both outdoor daylight and dark indoor shots, while manual is perfect for hands-on control.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; outline: none;">When using a wide angle lens, easy one-touch operation lets you take advantage of the built-in flash diffuser. With the FUJIFILM''s unique flash control technology "i Flash technology," the EF-X20 automatically optimizes the amount of light suitable to every shooting condition. It''s crafted from premium metal materials to compliment the design of the X-Series cameras with an ergonomic design for responsive dial control. The built-in wide diffuser can be selected by using the lever on the side of the flash.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; outline: none;"><strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; color: rgb(37, 37, 37);">Exposure setting dial</strong></p><ul style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; outline: none; list-style: none;"><li style="margin: 0px 0px 7px; padding: 0px; outline: none; list-style: disc inside;">Enables flash compensation from -1EV to +1EV in increments of 1/3 stops in the TTL Auto mode.</li><li style="margin: 0px 0px 7px; padding: 0px; outline: none; list-style: disc inside;">Enables flash output levels of 1/1, 1/2, 1/4, 1/8, 1/16, 1/32 and 1/64 in the Manual mode.</li><li style="margin: 0px 0px 7px; padding: 0px; outline: none; list-style: disc inside;">Immediate visual confirmation of settings even when the unit is turned OFF.</li></ul><p style="margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; outline: none;"><strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; color: rgb(37, 37, 37);">Lever for setting wide panel</strong><br style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none;">Raise the lever to support a focal length of down to 20mm (35mm film equivalent).</p><p style="margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; outline: none;"><strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; color: rgb(37, 37, 37);">Mounting lock releasing button</strong><br style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none;">The EF-X20 Shoe Mount Flash features a new mechanism that automatically locks the shoe-mount flash unit when it is placed on the hot shoe. The mechanism firmly fixes the flash unit in place without operating the locking bar or tightening the screw.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; outline: none;"><strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; color: rgb(37, 37, 37);">Wireless slave flash selector</strong><br style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none;">To use the unit as a master flash, set the switch to X. To use the unit as a slave flash, set the switch to N-MODE if the master flash is the "non-preflash" type and P-MODE if the master flash is the "preflash" type. The unit fires automatically upon detecting light from the master flash.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; outline: none;"><strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; color: rgb(37, 37, 37);">The Fuji EF-X20 Shoe Mount Flash is compatible with the following models:</strong></p><p style="margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px; outline: none;">FinePix X100 / HS30EXR / HS33EXR / HS25EXR / HS28EXR / HS20EXR / HS22EXR / SL300 / SL305 / SL280 / SL260 / SL240, FUJIFILM X10 / X-S1 / X-Pro1 / X-E1</p></div>', '<h2 style="margin-top: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; font-size: 2rem; color: rgb(37, 37, 37); font-family: proxima-nova, ''Helvetica Neue'', helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 2.2rem;">Additional Information</h2><table class="data-table" id="product-attribute-specs-table" style="margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; outline: none; border-collapse: separate; border-bottom-width: 0px; width: 614.1141357421875px; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: proxima-nova, ''Helvetica Neue'', helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 29.42943000793457px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><colgroup style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none;"><col width="25%" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none;"><col style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none;"></colgroup><tbody style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none;"><tr class="first odd" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none;"><th class="label" style="margin: 0px; padding: 5px 10px; outline: none; color: rgb(54, 54, 54); border-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);">Manufacturer</th><td class="data last" style="margin: 0px; padding: 10px; outline: none;">Fuji</td></tr><tr class="even" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241);"><th class="label" style="margin: 0px; padding: 5px 10px; outline: none; color: rgb(54, 54, 54); border-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);">Manufacturer SKU</th><td class="data last" style="margin: 0px; padding: 10px; outline: none;">16241307</td></tr><tr class="odd" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none;"><th class="label" style="margin: 0px; padding: 5px 10px; outline: none; color: rgb(54, 54, 54); border